    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1874-10-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1874-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                <head>No. 207.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Washburne</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1874-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 23,
                            1874</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 652.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to instruction No. 651, of the 21st
                        instant, I have to inform you that the watch intended to be restored to the
                        family of General Lafayette will be forwarded to you in a separate package
                        by this mail; and you are requested to ascertain the eldest male
                        representative of General Lafayette, and to restore the watch to him as the
                        representative of the family, in accordance with the provisions of the act
                        of Congress.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
